  "prompt": "What is the meaning of stress?",
  "response": "Stress refers to a state of mental or emotional strain resulting from demanding circumstances. It can also relate to physical pressure on an object or material. In a psychological context, stress occurs when an individual perceives that the demands placed on them exceed their coping resources, leading to feelings of anxiety, tension, and other responses.\n\nThere are two main types of stress:\n\n1. **Acute Stress**: This is short-term stress that arises from specific events or situations, such as exams, deadlines, or public speaking. It can be beneficial in motivating people to respond to challenges.\n\n2. **Chronic Stress**: This is long-term stress resulting from ongoing issues such as financial troubles, work demands, or relationship problems. Chronic stress can have serious health consequences if not managed effectively.\n\nStress can impact physical health, mental well-being, and overall quality of life, making it important to develop coping strategies and practices for stress management.",
